#####  DAST (Invcti)

🟩 Super Simple Example
❌ Before (Bad)

Your EC2 allows TLS 1.0
Certificate is close to expiry
No HSTS header

DAST report → fails

✔ After (Good)

Only TLS 1.2 and TLS 1.3 allowed
Certificate updated
Headers fixed

DAST report → passes

🟦 One‑Line Summary
TLS/SSL is the security system that protects data between users and your EC2 application.
DevOps manages and fixes TLS/SSL settings because they belong to infrastructure, not code.

-----------------------------

How Security Policies work (simple explanation)
A security policy is a bundle that defines:

Which TLS versions are allowed
Which ciphers are allowed
Whether TLS 1.3 is supported

Example policies:


Policy NameTLS SupportELBSecurityPolicy-2016-08TLS 1.0, 1.1, 
1.2ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS12-1-2017-01Only 
TLS 1.2ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-2-2021TLS 1.2 + TLS 1.3

############# Super Simple Summary
Check TLS version:

Open EC2 → Load Balancers
Select your ALB
Go to Listeners tab
Click HTTPS:443 → Edit
Change Security Policy to:

ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-2-2021
----------------
ALB → Look at Security Policy
EC2 → Check NGINX/Apache config or use curl test
----------------
Update TLS version:

ALB → Change Security Policy
EC2 → Modify ssl_protocols in config

Certificate does NOT auto-update.



###✅ How to Check a Certificate & How to Update (Renew) It

How to CHECK Certificate on AWS ALB
✅ Method 1: Check using AWS Console (Easiest)

Go to: EC2 → Load Balancers
Select your Application Load Balancer (ALB)
Go to Listeners tab
Click HTTPS : 443 → View/Edit
You will see:

Certificate: arn:aws:acm:region:account:certificate/xxxx


Click the certificate ARN → It opens ACM (AWS Certificate Manager.)
ACM will show:

Domain name
Certificate status (Issued / Expired / Inactive)
Expiration date
Issuer
Renewal eligibility

How to Update Certificate on AWS ALB

Jab AWS ACM tumhare certificate ko auto‑renew karta hai, toh woh hamesha naya 
certificate banata hai, jiska ARN bhi naya hota hai. Isliye ALB automatically us 
par switch nahi karta. Tumhe manually ALB ke HTTPS listener me jaa kar naya ARN 
select karna padta hai. Process simple hai: EC2 console me Load Balancer kholo, 
443 listener pe “Edit” karo, phir dropdown me se fresh renewed certificate 
(latest expiry date wala) choose karo aur save kar do. Jaise hi tum new ARN select 
karte ho, ALB turant updated certificate use karne lagta hai—certificate renewal 
future me fir se automatic hoga, lekin next renewal par fir se ek naya ARN banega, 
jise tumhe manually ya automation se dobara attach karna hoga. Matlab ACM renewal 
automatic hota hai, par ALB ko naya ARN manually attach karna padega, kyunki 
AWS automatically production load balancer ki 
certificate configuration change nahi karta, taa ki koi risk na ho.


















